x4freetext: Two-sections ionisation chamber of 17 l volume,
under presure of 10 atm, in cylinder cover of 28.2 cm
diameter and 27.3 cm high.Used gases - Ar, O, Kr,
for neutron beam monitoring. Calibrated by U-238
Energy resolution of alpha-spectrometer was defined
80 keV by alpha-source consisted of U-234,Pu-239,
Target -steel cylinder of 2 cm lengh and 1 cm
diameter with deyterium gas under presure 1.5-2 atm.
Error angles (0 deg. and 90 deg.) definition
